WEBVTT

00:05:58.125 --> 00:06:01.434
And we lose that capacity, right?

00:06:01.458 --> 00:06:04.976
So, over the years,
I've interviewed hundreds of people

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:08.101
from all backgrounds
and political affiliations,

00:06:08.125 --> 00:06:10.476
from the Midwest US to China,

00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:13.351
and I talked to people
about how are we feeling

00:06:13.375 --> 00:06:14.643
about what's happening.

00:06:14.667 --> 00:06:16.768
Not what opinions or beliefs.

00:06:16.792 --> 00:06:18.059
What are we feeling

00:06:18.083 --> 00:06:20.417
about what's going on
with your local environment,

00:06:20.441 --> 00:06:23.101
with your water, your soil,
the big picture.

00:06:23.125 --> 00:06:25.268
And what I hear from people

00:06:25.292 --> 00:06:27.684
almost across the board, I'm telling you,

00:06:27.708 --> 00:06:29.059
is a bind.

00:06:29.083 --> 00:06:32.893
People tell me at some point
in the conversation,